        <h3>Is this appropriate for severe problems?</h3>
        <div>
          <p>No, it’s not. If you or your peer counselor think you need more intensive help, then please consider trying formal therapy, or visiting a doctor. If it's an emergency, please seek emergency help such as 911 or the suicide prevention hotline (1.800.784.2433). </p>
					<br>

			<p>If you feel you might hurt yourself or others, this service cannot help you. If you are a resident of the U.S., please contact the suicide prevention hotline at 1.800.784.2433 for immediate help.</p>
            
        </div>
        <h3>How is my information kept confidential?</h3>
        <div>
          <p>
			We will only share your phone number with your chosen peer counselor, and we will never share your email address. You can also delete all your information permanently from our systems.</p>
			<br>

			<p>On the technical side, all incoming and outgoing transmissions through scouterapp.com are secured through the SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) protocol. Further, all data provided to us is encrypted before it is stored.</p>
        </div>
        <h3>Can I use medical insurance?</h3>
        <div>
          <p>
            Sorry, no. This isn't formal therapy, and insurance can't be used.
          </p>
